Using the power rule for integration $\int x^n dx = \frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1}$:

$$
\begin{aligned}
V &= \pi \left[ \frac{u^7}{7} + \frac{6u^6}{6} + \frac{9u^5}{5} \right]_{-2}^{0} \\
&= \pi \left[ \frac{u^7}{7} + u^6 + \frac{9u^5}{5} \right]_{-2}^{0}
\end{aligned}
$$

Finally, we find a common denominator (35) to combine the fractions:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{128}{7} &= \frac{640}{35} \\
64 &= \frac{2240}{35} \\
\frac{288}{5} &= \frac{2016}{35}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
V &= \pi \left( \frac{640 - 2240 + 2016}{35} \right) \\
&= \pi \left( \frac{416}{35} \right)
\end{aligned}
$$

$$V = \frac{416\pi}{35}$$
